Key Match Events: Angola's goalkeeper Neblu received a straight red card for handling outside the penalty area.
Gelson Dala scored the first goal for Angola despite being down to 10 men.
Namibia's Lubeni Pombili Haukongo received a second yellow card and was sent off.
Gelson Dala scored his second goal from the resulting free-kick.
Mabululu scored Angola's third goal with a stylish right-footed effort.
Post-Match Reflections: Angola progressed to the quarter-finals of the Africa Cup of Nations for just the third time.
Namibia's first-ever AFCON knockout fixture ended in disappointment.
Gelson Dala was named Flashscore Man of the Match.
